			<ns0:name>jvo...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/102292187274959663599/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">We currently do not run the stabilization passes on intermediate object files and libraries.  Some of the passes simply can't run without the whole program.

Noel brought up the point that we may want a clearer error message, for cases where we may end up linking different non-stable IR, and if we know that it will cause trouble:

https://codereview.chromium.org/13466021/

Given a nice error message, developer will then know that they need to do a clean rebuild.
